ENTRY            C2317   20260122   20260325   20260325       C254
SUBENT        C2317001   20260122   20260325   20260325       C254
BIB                  8         25
TITLE      Cross Sections and Isomer Ratios for the Isomeric
           Pair Y90g and Y90m in the Rb87(alpha,n) and Y89(d,p)
           Reactions
AUTHOR     (C.Riley,B.Linder)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,134,B559,1964)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRev.134.B559
INSTITUTE  (1USAFSU)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USAFSU) The Florida State University Tandem
           Van de Graaff accelerator.
DETECTOR   (NAICR,GEMUC) 3- x 3-in. NaI crystal.
METHOD     (CHSEP,ACTIV) After irradiation, the targets were
           dissolved in HCl; yttrium, strontium, and barium
           carriers were added and the solution was made
           strongly basic with NaOH to remove aluminum. After
           washing, the precipitate was dissolved in a small
           amount of concentrated HNO3, strontium and barium
           carriers were again added and then precipitated as
           nitrates with fuming nitric acid. The prepared
           samples were gamma counted as soon as possible flat
           against the aluminum shield of a NaI scintillation
           crystal. After a period of ten half-lives ( 32 h),
           the samples were beta counted with a lead shielded
           calibrated Geiger-Muller counter.
HISTORY    (20180613C) BP
           (20260117U) Minor correction in subs.3,5
ENDBIB              25
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           28
SUBENT        C2317002   20180613   20190926   20190924       C185
BIB                  5          8
REACTION   (37-RB-87(A,N)39-Y-90-G,,SIG)
SAMPLE     The rubidium targets were prepared by evaporating
           high-purity RbCl upon aluminum backings with a
           thickness of 1 mg/cm2 or less. The targets were then
           individually bombarded with 11-18-MeV alpha particles.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Estimated errors.
DECAY-DATA (39-Y-90-G,64.0HR,B-)
